Diagnosis. Both sexes with dark brown integument on head, legs and mesosoma (
Figs. 21–24
). Metasoma with bluish violet metallic reflections (
Figs. 22 and 24
). Body completely covered with brownish pilosity. Compound eyes red in live specimens. Female: fore elaiospathe with the anterior comb starting below the strigilis and extending to the apex of the forebasitarsus. Both elaiospathes with overlapping hairs.

Distribution. This species occurs exclusively in Chile , from III Atacama Region (Parque Nacional Llanos de Challe) to V Valparaíso Region (Putaendo). CHILE : (
